what can i do to buy this house my parents are trying to buy another house my dad has a good paying stable job but doesn't get approved because his credit is not great my mom doesn't get approved even though she has really good credit because she doesn't work what can we do to make the purchasing of this house possible any suggestions please thankyou unfortunately when applying for a mortgage the person with the higher salary is the one who's credit score counts as far as the loan approval is concerned with many banks your mother wouldn't even be able to be on the loan because she doesn't work your best bet is for your father to find someone willing to cosign the loan with him or they just need to take some time improve his credit and then look into buying a new home please don't listen to the people talking about your mother applying and stating an income while they don't check of the time to verify that there is employment that would be committing loan fraud there is an audit process in place and there's always that chance that the underwriters or the fraud investigation team will choose your parent's loan to scrutinize loan fraud is a serious offense that generally winds up in jail time Mortgage Credit card Money supply Citigroup Internet fraud Life insurance Debt Insurance Credit score Deflation (economics) Identity theft FairTax Bank Savings and loan association Predatory lending Bond 401(k) Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Plame affair Security (finance) Unemployment benefit Grandview, U.S.A. Personal finance Flat tax Surveillance Evan Mecham Gross domestic product Credit card fraud Slot machine Hillary Rodham Clinton ACORN Short selling Timeline of the Enron scandal Betting (poker) Economic inequality Blackjack Divorce Interest Article One of the United States Constitution 2004 U.S. presidential election controversy, voting machines 2005 trial of Michael Jackson Investment bank Economy of the United States Microeconomics Advance fee fra